-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PREAMBLE
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

A significant portion of this project was created with AI assistance.

Most of today’s AI models were trained on vast amounts of publicly available 
open-source code. This code was written by thousands of humans who shared 
their work in good faith, largely before it was known that such data would 
be used to train the models that built this project. 

I am choosing to close the loop.

By releasing this under the Good Faith License, I am giving back to the 
commons what the AI took from it. This is not a traditional copyright claim. 
This is a hybrid creation — part human, part machine — and I want it to flow 
freely back into the ecosystem so others can build on it, improve it, break 
it, sell it, or fork it. 

This is my way of saying thank you to every contributor whose work helped 
train the models that helped build this, whether they knew it would happen 
or not.

